fields.name: Khabib Nurmagomedov
fields.strengths: Elite grappling and top control, relentless pressure, exceptional cardio, mental toughness, unbreakable will
fields.weaknesses: Limited striking diversity, occasional vulnerability to body shots
fields.bio: Khabib "The Eagle" Nurmagomedov is a retired Russian mixed martial artist and former UFC Lightweight Champion. He is widely regarded as one of the greatest fighters in MMA history, retiring with an undefeated record of 29-0. Khabib's dominance was characterized by his unparalleled grappling skills and ability to control opponents on the ground. He was inducted into the UFC Hall of Fame on June 30, 2022.

fields.name: Conor McGregor
fields.strengths: Explosive knockout power, elite precision striking, mental warfare, fast starts, championship experience
fields.weaknesses: Grappling defense, cardio in later rounds, susceptibility to leg kicks
fields.bio: Conor "The Notorious" McGregor is a former UFC Featherweight and Lightweight Champion, renowned for his striking prowess and charismatic persona. He made history by becoming the first fighter to hold two UFC titles simultaneously. McGregor's notable victories include knockouts over José Aldo and Eddie Alvarez. His last win was a 40-second TKO against Donald Cerrone in January 2020. After a hiatus due to a leg injury sustained in July 2021, McGregor has hinted at a potential return to the octagon in 2025, possibly against Michael Chandler.

fields.weaknesses: Occasional defensive lapses, limited experience in lightweight division
fields.bio: Ilia "El Matador" Topuria is a Georgian-born Spanish mixed martial artist and former UFC Featherweight Champion. He captured the title by knocking out Alexander Volkanovski at UFC 298 in February 2024 and successfully defended it against Max Holloway at UFC 308 in October 2024. With a perfect 16-0 record, Topuria is known for his explosive striking and submission skills. In April 2025, he vacated his featherweight title to move up to the lightweight division, aiming for a championship bout against Islam Makhachev. Topuria has begun his training camp in preparation for his lightweight debut, which is speculated to take place at UFC 317 during the International Fight Week in June 2025.

fields.bio: Islam Makhachev is a Russian mixed martial artist competing in the UFC's lightweight division. A protégé of Khabib Nurmagomedov, Makhachev has established himself as a dominant force with a well-rounded skill set. He captured the UFC Lightweight Championship by submitting Charles Oliveira at UFC 280 in October 2022. Makhachev has since defended his title successfully against top contenders, including Alexander Volkanovski and Dustin Poirier. His most recent defense was a first-round submission victory over Renato Moicano at UFC 311 in January 2025. As of April 2025, Makhachev is considered one of the top pound-for-pound fighters in the UFC.

fields.weaknesses: Occasional defensive lapses, history of disciplinary issues, periods of inactivity
fields.bio: Jon "Bones" Jones is an American mixed martial artist competing in the UFC's heavyweight division. Widely regarded as one of the greatest fighters in MMA history, Jones became the youngest champion in UFC history at age 23 when he won the light heavyweight title in 2011. He successfully defended the title multiple times before moving up to heavyweight. In March 2023, Jones captured the vacant UFC Heavyweight Championship by submitting Ciryl Gane at UFC 285. He defended the title against Stipe Miocic at UFC 309 in November 2024, winning via third-round TKO. As of April 2025, Jones is expected to face interim champion Tom Aspinall in a title unification bout later this year.

fields.bio: Tom Aspinall is a British mixed martial artist competing in the UFC's heavyweight division. Aspinall successfully defended his interim title against Curtis Blaydes with another first-round knockout at UFC 304 in July 2024. As of April 2025, he is in discussions for a title unification bout with reigning champion Jon Jones.

fields.name: Carlos Prates
fields.strengths:
Exceptional knockout power, high striking accuracy, durability, and Muay Thai expertise
Prates has demonstrated a 4-0 record in the UFC with all wins by knockout, earning four Performance of the Night bonuses. His recent knockouts against Neil Magny, Li Jingliang, Charles Radtke, and Trevin Giles highlight his striking prowess, with seven knockdowns in four fights
fields.weaknesses:
Limited grappling defense, potential stamina concerns in longer fights, smoking habit
Despite being a BJJ black belt, Prates prefers striking and has faced criticism for defending only 11 takedown attempts in his UFC career. His admission of smoking half a pack a day (X posts) and past struggles with nutrition could impact stamina, especially in five-round main events like his upcoming fight against Ian Garry.
fields.bio: Carlos "The Nightmare" Prates is a Brazilian professional mixed martial artist born on August 17, 1993, in Taubaté, São Paulo. He began training Muay Thai at 15 to overcome troubled teenage years and later earned a BJJ black belt. After an early 5-4 MMA record, he honed his skills in Thailand, winning titles like Bangla Stadium Champion and Glory of Heroes Champ. Joining the UFC via Dana White's Contender Series in 2023, he debuted with a knockout of Trevin Giles in February 2024 and went 4-0 in his rookie year, earning Newcomer of the Year honors. Known for his stoic demeanor and knockout power, he’s ranked #13 in the welterweight division and headlines UFC Kansas City on April 26, 2025, against Ian Garry.

fields.bio: Brandon Royval is an American professional mixed martial artist competing in the UFC Flyweight division. Known for his dynamic grappling and aggressive style, he earned the nickname "Raw Dawg" and has climbed to the #1 ranking in the flyweight division as of February 2024. Royval made his UFC debut in May 2020 with a submission win over Tim Elliott, earning Fight of the Night honors. Notable victories include wins over Kai Kara-France, Rogerio Bontorin, Matt Schnell, Brandon Moreno (in a rematch), and Tatsuro Taira. His losses came against top contenders like Alexandre Pantoja and Brandon Moreno in earlier bouts. After pulling out of a March 2025 fight against Manel Kape due to concussions, he is scheduled to face Kape again on June 28, 2025, at UFC 317.

fields.name: Brandon Moreno
fields.strengths: Exceptional grappling and submission skills, relentless pace, resilience, strong heart
fields.weaknesses: Inconsistent striking power, occasional vulnerability against elite wrestlers
fields.bio: Brandon "The Assassin Baby" Moreno is a dynamic Mexican mixed martial artist who has defined the UFC Flyweight division with his heart and tenacity. Known for his thrilling trilogy with Deiveson Figueiredo and a historic championship run, Moreno has become one of the fan favorites in the sport. His ability to recover from adversity and finish fights with slick submissions or scrambles makes him a true underdog fighter turned champion.

fields.name: Joaquin Buckley
fields.strengths: Explosive striking power, dynamic athleticism, and finishing ability. Known for his viral spinning back kick knockout and relentless pressure in the octagon.
fields.weaknesses: Limited experience in five-round fights and sometimes exposed defensive vulnerabilities when facing high-level grapplers.
fields.bio: Nicknamed "New Mansa," Joaquin Buckley is an American mixed martial artist from St. Louis, Missouri. Beginning his professional career in 2014 and competing in organizations like Shamrock FC, Bellator MMA, and LFA, he gained widespread recognition after his jaw-dropping spinning back kick knockout of Impa Kasanganay in 2020. Now competing in the UFC welterweight division, Buckley has quickly become a dangerous contender, winning multiple Performance of the Night bonuses and aiming to use big victories against top opponents—such as his recent win over Colby Covington—as a springboard toward a title shot.
